          description: "Resident Evil Village is a 2021 survival horror game developed and published by Capcom. It is the sequel to Resident Evil 7: Biohazard. Players control Ethan Winters, who is searching for his kidnapped daughter after a fateful encounter with Chris Redfield, and finds himself in a village filled with mutant creatures. Village maintains the Resident Evil series' survival horror elements, but uses more action-oriented gameplay. Resident Evil Village was announced at the PlayStation 5 reveal event in June 2020 and was released on May 7, 2021, for Windows, PlayStation 4, PlayStation 5, Stadia, Xbox One, and Xbox Series X/S. It received generally favorable reviews, with praise for its gameplay, setting, and variety, but criticism for its puzzles, boss fights and performance problems on the Windows version; the increased focus on action divided opinion. Resident Evil Village won multiple year-end accolades, including Game of the Year at the Golden Joystick Awards.",
